<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-18T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-18T15:00:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1795</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-18T16:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2307. Your 3932. You can tell Professor <persName>Herron</persName>
                                for his personal guidance that in the opinion of the Department it
                                is just as well not to close any door. At the same time Department
                                does not think it wise to express any opinion or thought which could
                                be conveyed to the parties approaching <persName>Herron</persName>.
                                It does not seem possible any serious movement for peace could come
                                from Bavaria at this time.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>